We recommended that the Local Chief Executive improve compliance in property accounting and custodianship controls which may include:

a.	completion of the conduct of inventory taking of all PPEs owned by the agency, including those remained in the old Municipal Building and other offices not yet accounted for;

b.	preparation of the updated Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) including those PPE located outside of the new Municipal Building especially those that are stored in the old Municipal Building in the prescribed form as shown in Annex 49 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume II and submit the same to the auditor; 

c.	requiring the Municipal Accountant and Property Custodian to record and keep track of all movements of the PPE and conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records; and

d.	requiring the municipal officials concerned to ascertain the status of parcels of land owned by the Municipality with titling issues and work for the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Lubao, assuming funds have been provided therefor.

