We recommended that the Local Chief Executive –

a. reconstitute an Inventory Committee to include each Department Head to facilitate inventory taking by Office of all the property, plant and equipment of the Municipality;

b.         require the Acting Municipal Treasurer to (i) maintain Property Records starting with the current year’s acquisition and recent years’ acquisitions and aim for a yearly increase of coverage until all PPE items are covered; (ii) reconcile inventory results with property records and those maintained at the Accounting Office and isolate items not reconciled for easy reference in succeeding inventory taking; (iii) aim to reduce the number and amount of unreconciled PPE account balances;

c.         direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to prepare Acknowledgement Receipts for Equipment (ARE) for all PPE items, starting with current and recent years’ acquisitions until all items are covered and thereafter, renew the AREs at least every three years or whenever there is change of custodianship; and

d.         instruct the Inventory Committee to check the condition of the PPE and prepare a report thereon in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Reports (WMR), the damaged, obsolete and unserviceable PPE items identified in the course of inventory-taking and request for their immediate disposal.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to:

a. continue and sustain its effort on the implementation of the five basic environmental laws on preserving and protecting the environment required under R.A. No. 9003;   

b. comply with the submission of the additional requirements specified in the NSWC evaluation checklist for the approval of its Ten-Year Solid Waste Management Plan; 

c. instruct the Acting Solid Waste Management Officer to closely supervise and monitor the operations of the MRFs to sustain its compliant rating from the ECA;  

d. strictly enforce the Sangguniang Bayan ordinance on the “no segregation, no collection” policy.; and

e. strengthen information drive and awareness campaign on the regulations on solid waste management in coordination with the DepEd officials in the Municipality and barangay officials in order to sustain and improve further its compliance rating.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Acting Municipal Treasurer to strengthen internal control over collections by:
strictly adhering to the regulations requiring the deposit of collections daily and intact and;
posting daily entries in the cashbook the collections and deposits pursuant to Section 32 of the Manual on NGAS and ensuring that the balance thereof corresponds to the actual cash in vault by fund.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive – 
create an Inventory Committee to (i) conduct a physical count on the property, plant and equipment to determine existence and condition of the PPEs; (ii) submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) duly reconciled with the accounting and property records;

require the Municipal Accountant and the designated Property Officer to (i) continue the provision of subsidiary ledgers for  PPE items by aiming for the full completion of  the current and a percentage of recent years’ acquisition until all PPE items are covered; (ii) reconcile the respective records of the Accounting Office and Property Officer on PPE; 

create an appraisal committee for the unbooked parcels of land and record the same under the PPE account; and 

require the Municipal Treasurer or Supply Officer to ascertain the status of parcels of land owned by the Municipality with titling issues and work for the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Lubao, assuming funds have been provided therefore.
